\begin_layout Subsubsection
Under a two-fold double nested normal error DGP 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Clustering is unlikely to have an impact on the estimates' bias.
 In this instance the source and target data differ.
 This is done to see the impact of applying a model estimated on a given
 set of clusters and applied to a possibly different set of clusters.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In small area estimation, 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citet
key "ea7f7e4f-7381-39b0-abdd-8da14c150408"
literal "false"

\end_inset

 suggest that modeling cluster effects at a level misaligned with the level
 of reporting can bias noise estimates.
 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citet
key "corral2021map"
literal "false"

\end_inset

 reinforce this point using model-based simulations but show that the bias
 of point estimates remains unaffected.
 In our case, since we report national-level estimates, ignoring random
 location effects does not compromise validity.
 This is evident in the simulation of Figure 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "fig:bias_eb_mi-2"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

, which uses a two-stage sample drawn from a clustered data-generating process
 (see Annex 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "subsec:DGP_cluster"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

).
 The figure compares models that account for clustering (one-fold and two-fold)
 with a model that ignores it (“Fixed-B”, 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

MI 20
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

, and 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

MI 100
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

) and shows that all three produce similar bias profiles.
 All result in low bias, at worst it is a little under 0.06 percentage points.
 The results shown here underscore that accounting for clustering is not
 critical for point estimates at the national level, though it does matter
 for the precision of subnational estimates (see 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citet
key "ea7f7e4f-7381-39b0-abdd-8da14c150408,corral2021map"
literal "false"

\end_inset

 ).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Float figure
